ation of her diverse and long-ranging career, getting her start in Hollywood as an actress in her teens and twenties, directing her first films in her early thirties, and later working as an acclaimed director of television westerns, sitcoms, and suspense dramas. It also demonstrates how Lupino fused generic elements of film noir and the social problem film to create a distinctive directorial style that was both highly expressionistic and grittily realistic. Ida Lupino, Director thus shines a long-awaited spotlight on one of our greatest filmmakers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  ahollywood, postwar hollywood, movies, directing, filmmaking, filmmaker, auteur, thirties, television, western, sitcom, suspense, drama, noir, film noir, writer, television writer, hays, hays code, visual culture, film, film studies, female director, female directors.1 aGrossman, Julie, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066609040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081357493640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813574936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813574936.jpg  a978-3-11-066609-0  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK